==English==

===Etymology===
* First attested in 1614.
* From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term/t|la|acclīvitās}}, from {{term/t|la|acclīvis||ascending}}, from {{term|ad|lang=la}} + {{term/t|la|clīvus||slope}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ə.ˈklɪv.ə.ti/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|acclivities}}

# {{context|geomorphology|lang=en}} A slope or inclination of the earth, as the side of a hill, considered as ''ascending'', in opposition to ''[[declivity]]'', or ''descending''; an upward slope; [[ascent]].

